<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-16T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-16T01:00:00-05:00" n="11" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.24/3493/12: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-16T09:00:00+03:00">May 16,
                                    1942—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 9:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>779. Department’s 410, May 8, midnight, last paragraph. If the Department
                            has not yet selected the representative for civilian supplies on the
                            Middle East Supply Center, General Maxwell suggests that Fred Winant now
                            in the Department is well qualified.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>